headline.main: BALKAN ECONOMICS TO FEATURE PARLEY; Foreign Ministers in Meeting Tomorrow Expected to Seek Means of Cooperation WOULD INCLUDE BULGARIA Hope to Avoid Entanglement in Effects of Blockade and Germany's Demands

lead_paragraph: BELGRADE, Yugoslavia, Jan. 31 --The official schedule of the Balkan Entente meeting was given out today. Premier and Foreign Minister John Metaxas of Greece and Foreign Minister Shukru Saragoglu of Turkey will arrive tomorrow evening, journeying from Nish, a town near the Bulgarian frontier.
